{{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Hulkamania: Let The Battle Begin |image= |caption= |alt= |tagline= |theme= |promotion= |date=2009 |attendance=5,000 |venue= *[[Rod Laver Arena]] *[[Burswood Dome]] *[[Brisbane Entertainment Centre]] *[[Acer Arena]] |city= *[[Melbourne]] *[[Perth]] *[[Brisbane]] *[[Sydney]] |lastevent= |nextevent= |event= |lastevent2= |nextevent2= }} '''Hulkamania: Let The Battle Begin Tour''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[international]] event held by [[Hulk Hogan]] and [[Eric Bischoff]] which took place in [[Australia]]. The event was taped by [[ONE HD]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://australiansportsentertainment.blogspot.com.au/2009/11/hulkamania-tour-australia-21st-november.html|title=Australian Sports Entertainment: Hulkamania Tour - Australia - 21st November 2009|last=Man|first=Media|date=2009-11-21|website=Australian Sports Entertainment|access-date=2018-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/Arena_Reports_10/article_36909.shtml#.VRPfxnaJjoo|title=PWTorch.com - 11/21 Hulkamania Tour in Melbourne: Very detailed report on Hulk Hogan and Ric Flair's first matches back, Hogan and Flair bleed heavily, Undercard matches re-create Attitude Era|website=pwtorch.com|access-date=2018-01-15}}</ref>
==Background== The main event heading into the event was between [[Hulk Hogan]] and [[Ric Flair]]. Flair came out of retirement for this.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mediaman.com.au/articles/hulkamania_let.html|title=Hulkamania Let The Battle Begin at Star City Casino gets out of control; Ric Flair attacks Hulk Hogan Media Man|website=www.mediaman.com.au|access-date=2018-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mediaman.com.au/profiles/hulkamania_let.html|title=Hulkamania Let The Battle Begin Hulk Hogan Wrestling living legend and icon Former WWE and WCW Champion Hollywood Hulk Hogan Hulkamania Media Man Australia|website=www.mediaman.com.au|access-date=2018-01-15}}</ref>
[[File:Hogan gathers himself.jpg|thumb|left|Hogan during a match against [[Ric Flair]] in 2009.]] On November 21, 24, 26, and 28, Hogan performed with a group of wrestlers including [[Matt Cross (wrestler)|Spartan-3000]], [[Jon Heidenreich|Heidenreich]], [[Eugene (wrestler)|Eugene]], [[Brutus Beefcake|Brutus "The Barber" Beefcake]] and [[Orlando Jordan]] across [[Australia]] in a tour titled ''Hulkamania: Let the Battle Begin''. The main event of each show was a rematch between Hogan and [[Ric Flair]]—the wrestler who defeated Hogan more times than any other. Hogan defeated Flair in all four matches, bringing his career record against Flair from 2–8 to 6–8.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://premier.ticketek.com.au/shows/show.aspx?sh=HulkAMAN09&v=SSD&searchId=278c866e-8461-4b0c-a20c-082bfcf71b96 |title=Hulkamania: Let the Battle Begin |publisher=Tickettek |accessdate=2009-11-05}}</ref> It was the first time Hogan had performed in Australia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.perthnow.com.au/news/western-australia/Hulk-hogan-downs-ric-flair-in-burswood-bout/story-e6frg13u-1225803762480|title=Hulk Hogan downs Ric Flair in Burswood bout|date=November 25, 2009|last=Elborough|first=Brad|publisher=Perth Now}}</ref>
On November 21, 2009, Flair returned to the ring as a [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heel]] on the Hulkamania: Let the Battle Begin tour of Australia, losing to Hulk Hogan in the main event of the first show by brassknuckles.<ref name=OWOW>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/profiles/r/ric-flair.html|accessdate=August 29, 2008|title=OWOW profile|publisher=Online World of Wrestling}}</ref> Hogan defeated Flair again on November 24 in Perth, Australia, after both men bled heavily.<ref name=OWOW/> Flair also lost to Hogan on the two remaining matches on the tour.<ref name=OWOW/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/Arena_Reports_10/article_36909.shtml|title=11/21 Hulkamania Tour in Melbourne: Very detailed report on Hulk Hogan and Ric Flair's first matches back, Hogan and Flair bleed heavily, Undercard matches re-create Attitude Era|last=Pilone|first=Antonio|date=November 21, 2009|work=PWTorch|accessdate=November 21, 2009}}</ref>
On November 21 [[Lacey Von Erich]] won a bikini contest, which also included Koa Marie Turner, Stephanie Pietz and Kiara Dillon. She also interfered in the main event between Hogan and [[Ric Flair]], on Flair's behalf.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/Arena_Reports_10/article_36909.shtml|title=11/21 Hulkamania Tour in Melbourne: Very detailed report on Hulk Hogan and Ric Flair's first matches back, Hogan and Flair bleed heavily, Undercard matches re-create Attitude Era|last=Pilone|first=Antonio|date=2009-11-21|accessdate=2009-11-21|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> In other matches on the tour she was used as Flair's manager.<ref name=OWOW/>
There was talk of another tour in China and other parts of Asia, however after the unsuccessful Australian tour, those plans fell through.
[[File:Hogan Vs Flair.jpg|thumb|The Main Event of Hulkamania Tour in 2009, [[Ric Flair]] vs. [[Hulk Hogan]].]]
