==Home Release== Despite having television cameras present, this event has never been released on DVD.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestlinginc.com/wi/news/2010/0225/526053/hulkamania-tour-company-bankrupt/|title='Hulkamania Tour' Company Bankrupt|last=|first=|date=2010-10-25|accessdate=2010-10-25|publisher=Wrestling Inc.}}</ref>
The company behind the tour filed for bankruptcy shortly after the final event and the advertised DVD of the tour is not expected to be released. Hogan reportedly wouldn't allow them to market the DVD until the promoters paid him money he was still owed for the tour. The show was scheduled to air in Australia not long after the events took place but they were also cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sescoops.com/hulkamania-tour-company-bankrupt-orlando-jordan-storyline/|title=Hulkamania Tour Company Bankrupt, Orlando Jordan Storyline|last=|first=|date=2010-10-25|accessdate=2010-10-25|publisher=SE Scoops.}}</ref>
