''Life Is Strange'' received generally favourable reviews, with a Metacritic score of 85/100 on PlayStation 4 and Xbox One.<ref name="aggregated">{{cite web|url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/life-is-good-dontnod-on-the-success-of-life-is-strange-and-what-comes-next/0164045 |title=Life is good: Dontnod on the success of Life is Strange and what comes next |first=Alex |last=Calvin |date=15 March 2016 |work=[[Market for Home Computing and Video Games|MCV]] |accessdate=16 March 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317064842/http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/life-is-good-dontnod-on-the-success-of-life-is-strange-and-what-comes-next/0164045 |archivedate=17 March 2016  }}</ref> While some reviewers criticised the games's [[Lip sync#In video games|lip-syncing]]<ref name="lip sync 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-1-ps4-review-be-kind-rewind|title=Life is Strange, Episode 1 PS4 Review: Be Kind, Rewind|first=Mike|last=Williams|date=2 February 2015|work=[[Eurogamer#Subsidiaries|USgamer]]|accessdate=21 July 2015|archivedate=11 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150211212247/http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-1-ps4-review-be-kind-rewind|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="lip sync 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamezone.com/videos/life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis-video-review-44v |title=Life is Strange Episode 1: Chrysalis Video Review |work=GameZone |accessdate=22 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906190802/http://www.gamezone.com/videos/life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis-video-review-44v |archivedate=6 September 2015  }}</ref><ref name="sleeper hit" /> and use of dated [[slang]],<ref name="sleeper hit" /><ref name="slang 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/1/29/7945795/life-is-strange-review-xbox-one-ps4-360-ps3-PC-episode-one|title=Life is Strange: Episode One – Chrysalis review: so-called life|first1=Megan|last1=Farokhmanesh|first2=Colin|last2=Campbell|date=29 January 2015|work=[[Polygon]]|accessdate=10 March 2015|archivedate=30 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130172551/http://www.polygon.com/2015/1/29/7945795/life-is-strange-review-xbox-one-ps4-360-ps3-PC-episode-one|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="slang 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/life-is-strange-episode-one-review/ |title=Life Is Strange |first=Cassandra |last=Khaw |date=10 February 2015 |work=[[PC Gamer]] |accessdate=24 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151009220905/http://www.pcgamer.com/life-is-strange-episode-one-review/ |archivedate=9 October 2015  }}</ref> they lauded the character development<ref name="sleeper hit" /><ref name="character 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/01/29/life-strange-episode-1-review-chrysalis|title='Life Is Strange' Episode 1 review: 'Chrysalis'|first=Jonathon|last=Dornbush|date=29 January 2015|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=10 March 2015|archivedate=2 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202002140/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/01/29/life-strange-episode-1-review-chrysalis|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="character 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/life-is-strange-review/ |title=Life Is Strange |first=Phil |last=Savage |date=22 October 2015 |work=[[PC Gamer]] |accessdate=22 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023185424/http://www.pcgamer.com/life-is-strange-review/ |archivedate=23 October 2015  }}</ref> and time travel component,<ref name="sleeper hit" /><ref name="time travel 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|title=Review: Life is Strange Episode 1: Chrysalis|first=Geoff|last=Thew|date=29 January 2015|work=[[Hardcore Gamer]]|accessdate=10 March 2015|archivedate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131002234/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="time travel 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.shacknews.com/article/91829/life-is-strange-review-selfie-destruction |title=Life is Strange review: 'Selfie'-destruction |first=Ozzie |last=Mejia |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Shacknews]] |accessdate=21 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023164732/http://www.shacknews.com/article/91829/life-is-strange-review-selfie-destruction |archivedate=23 October 2015  }}</ref> suggesting that there should be more games like it.<ref name="suggest 2">{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2015/01/life-is-strange-episode-one-review-trying-and-retrying-new-things/ |title=Life is Strange Episode One review: Trying and retrying new things |first=Steven |last=Strom |date=30 January 2015 |work=[[Ars Technica]] |accessdate=22 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022231404/http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2015/01/life-is-strange-episode-one-review-trying-and-retrying-new-things/ |archivedate=22 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="suggest 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|title=Review: Life is Strange Episode 1: Chrysalis|first=Geoff|last=Thew|date=29 January 2015|work=[[Hardcore Gamer]]|accessdate=21 July 2015|archivedate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131002234/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|deadurl=no}}</ref> ''[[Eurogamer]]'' said it was "one of the best interactive story games of this generation"<ref name="full season">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-10-22-life-is-strange |title=Life is Strange review |first=Aoife |last=Wilson |date=22 October 2015 |work=[[Eurogamer]] |accessdate=22 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022200126/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-10-22-life-is-strange |archivedate=22 October 2015  }}</ref> and ''[[Hardcore Gamer]]'' said it was the [[sleeper hit]] of 2015.<ref name="sleeper hit">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/11/07/review-life-is-strange/175508/|title=Review: Life Is Strange|last=Riaz|first=Adnan|date=7 November 2015|website=|work=[[Hardcore Gamer]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151108212519/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/11/07/review-life-is-strange/175508/|archivedate=8 November 2015|deadurl=no|accessdate=7 November 2015}}</ref> ''Life Is Strange'' received over 75 Game of the Year awards and listings.<ref name="writers" /> In April 2017, ''Xbox One UK'' ranked it first in its list of Xbox One games priced under {{GB£|20}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xboxoneuk.com/xbox-one/xbouks-top-20-games-for-under-20|title=XBOUK's Top 20 Games For Under £20|first=Stephen|last=Loftus|date=25 April 2017|website=Xbox One UK|archivedate=1 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170601063704/http://www.xboxoneuk.com/xbox-one/best-20-xbox-one-games-for-under-20/|deadurl=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Game director [[Yoko Taro]] listed it as one of his favourite PlayStation 4 games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.us.playstation.com/2017/07/11/discover-the-creators-yoko-taros-favorite-ps4-games/|title=Discover the Creators: Yoko Taro's Favorite PS4 Games|author=[[Yoko Taro|Taro, Yoko]]|date=11 July 2017|website=[[PlayStation Blog]]|archivedate=11 July 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170711163205/https://blog.us.playstation.com/2017/07/11/discover-the-creators-yoko-taros-favorite-ps4-games/|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
[[File:GDC 2016 awards 16-20 52 32-01-7D1 0959 (25731583212).jpg|thumb|left|The developers accept the audience award at the 2016 [[Game Developers Choice Awards|GDC Awards]].]]
Kevin VanOrd of ''[[GameSpot]]'' said ''Episode 1: Chrysalis''{{ref|2|2}} is "an involving [[slice of life]] that works because its situations eloquently capture a peculiar early-college state of mind",<ref name="slice of life">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-one-review/1900-6416015/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode One Review |first=Kevin |last=VanOrd |date=29 January 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024065018/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-one-review/1900-6416015/ |archivedate=24 October 2015  }}</ref> while ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s Kimberley Wallace said the game's tackling of "subjects that are usually [[taboo]] for video games" was impressive.<ref name="taboo">{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange/b/pc/archive/2015/01/29/life-is-strange-episode-one-chrysalis-review-game-informer.aspx |title=A Promising And Exciting Debut |first=Kimberley |last=Wallace |date=29 January 2015 |work=[[Game Informer]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151020151045/http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange/b/pc/archive/2015/01/29/life-is-strange-episode-one-chrysalis-review-game-informer.aspx |archivedate=20 October 2015  }}</ref> ''[[Destructoid]]''{{'}}s Brett Makedonski said the episode's strongest characteristic was exploration—both "[[self]]- and worldly".<ref name="self- and worldly">{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/review-life-is-strange-chrysalis-286926.phtml |title=Review: Life is Strange: Chrysalis |first=Brett |last=Makedonski |date=29 January 2015 |work=[[Destructoid]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151108031815/http://www.destructoid.com/review-life-is-strange-chrysalis-286926.phtml |archivedate=8 November 2015  }}</ref> Mitch Dyer of ''[[IGN]]'' said the story was ultimately obstructed by its "laughable" script and "worse performances".<ref name="obstruct">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/02/life-is-strange-episode-1-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode 1 Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=2 February 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151025110238/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/02/life-is-strange-episode-1-review |archivedate=25 October 2015  }}</ref> In response to ''Episode 2: Out of Time'', ''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]''{{'}}s Megan Farokhmanesh also said that the emphasis on self-exploration had considerable impact on the enjoyment of the game.<ref name="self-exploration">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/3/25/8291203/life-is-strange-episode-two-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode Two – Out of Time review: stand by me |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=25 March 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226163422/http://www.polygon.com/2015/3/25/8291203/life-is-strange-episode-two-review |archivedate=26 December 2015  }}</ref> Other critics said the ending was an "emotional high point" and that it brought meaning to the choices from both the first and second episodes.<ref name="emotional high point">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-two-review/1900-6416079/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode Two Review |first=Alexa Ray |last=Corriea |date=26 March 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016054649/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-two-review/1900-6416079/ |archivedate=16 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="meaning">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/24/life-is-strange-episode-2-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode 2 Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=24 March 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030235124/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/24/life-is-strange-episode-2-review |archivedate=30 October 2015  }}</ref> Mike Williams said in ''USgamer'' that the pacing of ''Episode 2: Out of Time'' was "slower and less exciting" than that of episode one.<ref name="disparaged">{{cite web|url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-2-ps4-review |title=Life is Strange, Episode 2 PS4 Review: The Magical and The Mundane |first=Mike |last=Williams |date=27 March 2015 |work=[[Eurogamer#Subsidiaries|USgamer]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117155701/http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-2-ps4-review |archivedate=17 November 2015  }}</ref>

Adnan Riaz of ''Hardcore Gamer'' said ''Episode 3: Chaos Theory'' was a dramatic improvement that presented a "thrilling, poignant, fascinating and&nbsp;... enticing" narrative whose outcome from past decisions also added a sense of realism.<ref name="enticing">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/05/22/review-life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory/149654/ |title=Review: Life Is Strange Episode 3: Chaos Theory |first=Adnan |last=Riaz |date=22 May 2015 |work=[[Hardcore Gamer]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117031924/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/05/22/review-life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory/149654/ |archivedate=17 November 2015  }}</ref> Peter Paras of ''[[Game Revolution]]'' complimented the character beats, particularly the development of Chloe Price, who he said "really comes into her own as [a] fully-formed character".<ref name="fully-formed">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory |title=Life Is Strange: Episode 3 – Chaos Theory Review |first=Peter |last=Paras |date=19 May 2015 |work=[[Game Revolution]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151012041001/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory |archivedate=12 October 2015  }}</ref> Though ''GameSpot''{{'}}s Alexa Ray Corriea said that the [[Quest (video gaming)#Gather quests|fetch quests]] interfered with its emotional quality,<ref name="interfere">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-three-review/1900-6416147/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode Three Review |first=Alexa Ray |last=Corriea |date=20 May 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102040010/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-three-review/1900-6416147/ |archivedate=2 November 2015  }}</ref> the episode built up to a "killer cliffhanger" according to Farokhmanesh.<ref name="killer">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/1/8688317/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode Three – Chaos Theory review: echo chamber |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=1 June 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018115049/http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/1/8688317/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory-review |archivedate=18 October 2015  }}</ref> ''GameZone''{{'}}s Matt Liebl said ''Episode 4: Dark Room'' was "easily the most emotional episode" and that the mystery of Rachel Amber had done a "tremendous job in keeping us hooked".<ref name="mystery">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review-jv9v |title=Life is Strange Episode 4: Dark Room Review |first=Matt |last=Liebl |date=30 July 2015 |work=GameZone |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023163037/http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review-jv9v |archivedate=23 October 2015  }}</ref> Tom Hoggins of ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]'' said the developer's venture into subjects like [[Social class|social division]], [[Cyberbullying|online bullying]], parental conflict and [[suicide]] as "bold".<ref name="bold">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/what-to-play/life-is-strange-episode-4-review/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode 4, The Dark Room: 'Precariously balanced' |first=Tom |last=Hoggins |date=11 August 2015 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015013926/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/what-to-play/life-is-strange-episode-4-review/ |archivedate=15 October 2015  }}</ref> Critics said there were [[Tone (literature)|tonal]] problems, caused by the game's "cheap ways" of progressing the plot, such as character inconsistency and superfluous [[shock value]].<ref name="cheap 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/07/30/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review |title=Life Is Strange – Episode 4: Dark Room Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=30 July 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102014136/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/07/30/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review |archivedate=2 November 2015  }}</ref><ref name="cheap 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-four-review/1900-6416204/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode Four Review |first=Alexa Ray |last=Corriea |date=28 July 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151028230540/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-four-review/1900-6416204/ |archivedate=28 October 2015  }}</ref> Critics were more favourable towards the episode's puzzles and relationships.<ref name="puzzles">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/8/13/9130223/life-is-strange-episode-4-review-dark-room |title=Life is Strange: Episode Four – Dark Room review: low road |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=13 August 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024070210/http://www.polygon.com/2015/8/13/9130223/life-is-strange-episode-4-review-dark-room |archivedate=24 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="relationships">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange--episode-4-the-dark-room |title=Life Is Strange – Episode 4: The Dark Room Review |first=Peter |last=Paras |date=6 August 2015 |work=[[Game Revolution]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117020622/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange--episode-4-the-dark-room |archivedate=17 November 2015  }}</ref> They said the final episode, ''Polarized'', had a "fitting conclusion" to the [[coming of age]] story of Max Caulfield and the relationship between the two leads was carried out successfully.<ref name="of age">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/10/26/review-life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized/173583/ |title=Review: Life Is Strange Episode 5: Polarized |first=Adnan |last=Riaz |date=26 October 2015 |work=[[Hardcore Gamer]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151028195126/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/10/26/review-life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized/173583/ |archivedate=28 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="two leads">{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange_episode_5_-_polarized/b/playstation4/archive/2015/10/21/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review-game-informer.aspx |title=Life is Strange: Episode 5 – Polarized |first=Kimberley |last=Wallace |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Game Informer]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030031739/http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange_episode_5_-_polarized/b/playstation4/archive/2015/10/21/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review-game-informer.aspx |archivedate=30 October 2015  }}</ref> One stealth sequence was described as "tedious" and "out-of-place" while other aspects inhabiting the same course of events were favoured.<ref name="tedious">{{cite web|url=http://www.themarysue.com/life-really-is-strange/ |title=Review: Life Is Strange Episode 5: "Polarized" AKA Let's Have a Feels Trip |first=Jessica |last=Lachenal |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Dan Abrams#The Mary Sue|The Mary Sue]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024003355/http://www.themarysue.com/life-really-is-strange/ |archivedate=24 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="out-of-place">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/22/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review |title=Life Is Strange – Episode 5: Polarized Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104092509/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/22/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review |archivedate=4 November 2015  }}</ref> Reviewers were divided on the ending.<ref name="good 2">{{cite web|url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-5-review |title=Life is Strange Episode 5 PS4 Review: Time to Let Things Go |first=Mike |last=Williams |date=23 October 2015 |work=[[Eurogamer#Subsidiaries|USgamer]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151027235637/http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-5-review |archivedate=27 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="good 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/10/21/9589174/life-is-strange-episode-5-review-polarized |title=Life is Strange: Episode Five – Polarized review |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151029223907/http://www.polygon.com/2015/10/21/9589174/life-is-strange-episode-5-review-polarized |archivedate=29 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="bad 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/life-strange-review/ |title=Life is Strange review |first=Ashley |last=Reed |date=22 October 2015 |work=[[GamesRadar]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018033822/http://www.gamesradar.com/life-strange-review/ |archivedate=18 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name="bad 2">{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/life-is-stranges-ending-is-a-hot-mess-1738291856 |title=Life is Strange's Ending Is A Hot Mess |first=Patricia |last=Hernandez |date=23 October 2015 |work=[[Kotaku]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030015945/http://kotaku.com/life-is-stranges-ending-is-a-hot-mess-1738291856 |archivedate=30 October 2015  }}</ref>

===Sales===
The first episode was ranked fifth among the best selling PlayStation 3 and PlayStation 4 video games of February 2015.<ref name="february sales">{{cite web|url=http://blog.us.playstation.com/2015/03/12/playstation-store-february-2015s-top-sellers/|title=PlayStation Store: February 2015's Top Sellers|first=Justin|last=Massongill|date=12 March 2015|work=[[PlayStation Blog]]|accessdate=12 March 2015|archivedate=15 March 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150315053212/http://blog.us.playstation.com/2015/03/12/playstation-store-february-2015s-top-sellers/|deadurl=no}}</ref> ''Life Is Strange'' reached one million sales in July 2015,<ref name="july sales">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/07/23/life-is-strange-hits-1-million-sales-episode-4-release-date-announced |title=Life is Strange Hits 1 Million Sales, Episode 4 Release Date Announced |first=Luke |last=Karmali |date=23 July 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=23 July 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725000242/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/07/23/life-is-strange-hits-1-million-sales-episode-4-release-date-announced |archivedate=25 July 2015  }}</ref> having accumulated over 1.2 million unique players worldwide; the [[attach rate]] to units between the complete season and [[Season ticket#Other uses|season pass]] proved to be "extremely strong", divulged Square Enix.<ref name="unique players">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/7/23/9022561/life-is-strange-episode-4-release-date-trailer |title=Life is Strange hits 1M copies sold, fourth episode coming next week |first=Samit |last=Sarkar |date=23 July 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=24 July 2015 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725015350/http://www.polygon.com/2015/7/23/9022561/life-is-strange-episode-4-release-date-trailer |archivedate=25 July 2015  }}</ref> The retail edition made seventh place in the top ten [[United Kingdom|UK]] game sales chart for the week ending 23 January 2016.<ref name="uk sales">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-duty-black-ops-3-camps-at-top-of-uk-chart/1100-6434106/ |title=Call of Duty: Black Ops 3 Camps at Top of UK Chart |first=Tamoor |last=Hussain |date=25 January 2016 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=26 January 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128033016/http://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-duty-black-ops-3-camps-at-top-of-uk-chart/1100-6434106/ |archivedate=28 January 2016  }}</ref> ''Life Is Strange'' was one of the top 100 best-selling games on Steam in 2016.<ref name="dry ice">{{cite web|url=http://store.steampowered.com/sale/2016_top_sellers/ |title=Top 100 |website=[[Steam (software)|Steam]] |publisher=[[Valve Corporation]] |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102152559/http://store.steampowered.com/sale/2016_top_sellers/ |archivedate=2 January 2017  }}</ref> As of May 2017, more than three million copies have been sold.<ref name="c0p135">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-05-18-life-is-strange-2-finally-confirmed |title=Life is Strange 2 finally confirmed |first=Tom |last=Phillips |date=18 May 2017 |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518213403/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-05-18-life-is-strange-2-finally-confirmed |archivedate=18 May 2017  }}</ref><ref name="1nth3w0rk5">{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/a-new-life-is-strange-game-is-in-the-works-436830.phtml|title=A new Life is Strange game is in the works|first=Ray|last=Porreca|date=18 May 2017|website=[[Destructoid]]|publisher=[[ModernMethod]]|archivedate=1 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170601064007/https://www.destructoid.com/a-new-life-is-strange-game-is-in-the-works-436830.phtml|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

