==Legacy==
After ''Life Is Strange'' achieved financial and commercial success, Dontnod Entertainment started to become more prominent in the video game industry; publishers pursued the studio for the first time, whereas they previously had to pursue publishers themselves. CEO Oskar Guilbert said that the game saved his company financially after the mediocre sales of ''[[Remember Me (video game)|Remember Me]]''.<ref name="solicited success">{{cite web|url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/how-life-is-strange-changed-dontnod/0174354 |title=How Life is Strange changed Dontnod |first=Christopher |last=Dring |date=25 October 2016 |website=[[The Market for Computer & Video Games|MCV]] |accessdate=25 October 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026080029/http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/how-life-is-strange-changed-dontnod/0174354 |archivedate=26 October 2016  }}</ref>

In 2016, Square Enix sponsored its own "Everyday Heroes" photography contest, inspired by the game, offering a {{USD|10,000}} scholarship for the winning entry.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2016/1/26/10834900/life-is-strange-everyday-heroes-scholarship-fund-contest | title = Life is Strange sponsors actual Everyday Heroes photo contest | first = Allegra | last = Frank  |date = 26 January 2016 | accessdate = 1 October 2018 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref> Square Enix also coordinated with Parent Advocacy Coalition for Educational Rights (PACER) to support an anti-bullying inititive based on themes within the game.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2016/1/13/10763900/life-is-strange-everyday-heroes-pacer-national-bullying-prevention | title = Life is Strange charity challenge asks 'everyday heroes' to prevent bullying | first = Allegra | last =Frank | date = 13 January 2016 | accessdate = 1 October 2018 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref>

In July 2016, [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary Digital Studios]] and Square Enix, in conjunction with dj2 Entertainment announced that they would be adapting ''Life Is Strange'' as a digital series.<ref name="adaptation">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/legendary-tackling-adaptation-life-is-914899 |title=Legendary Tackling Adaptation of 'Life Is Strange' Video Game (Exclusive) |first=Borys |last=Kit |date=27 July 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=27 July 2016 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728134633/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/legendary-tackling-adaptation-life-is-914899 |archivedate=28 July 2016  }}</ref> Legendary said that, at the time of the announcement, they were meeting with potential writers for the series adaptation, which would be set in Arcadia Bay.<ref name="writers">{{cite web|url=https://www.legendary.com/legendary-digital-studios-partners-with-square-enix-and-dj2-to-adapt-award-winning-episodic-videogame-life-is-strange-into-digital-series/|title=Legendary Digital Studios Partners with Square Enix and dj2 to Adapt Award Winning Episodic Videogame Life Is Strange into Digital Series|date=27 July 2016|work=[[Legendary Entertainment]]|accessdate=30 July 2016|archivedate=1 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170601063430/https://www.legendary.com/legendary-digital-studios-partners-with-square-enix-and-dj2-to-adapt-award-winning-episodic-videogame-life-is-strange-into-digital-series/|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ''[[Life Is Strange: Before the Storm]]'', a three-part prequel developed by [[Deck Nine]], launched on 31 August 2017.<ref name="b3f0r3th35t0rm">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2017/6/11/15779506/life-is-strange-prequel-before-the-storm-release-date|title=Life is Strange prequel Before the Storm debuts this summer (update)|first=Samit|last=Sarkar|date=11 June 2017|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|archivedate=12 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170612033310/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2017/6/11/15779506/life-is-strange-prequel-before-the-storm-release-date|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref> A free [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] called ''[[The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit]]'' was announced and released in June 2018.<ref name="The Verge">{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/10/17446874/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-release-date-life-is-strange |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180610210842/https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/10/17446874/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-release-date-life-is-strange |title=New Life is Strange game, The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit, coming June 26th |last=Farokhmanesh |first=Megan |website=[[The Verge]] |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |archivedate=10 June 2018 |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Engadget">{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2018/06/10/life-is-strange-awesome-adventures-captain-spirit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180610211011/https://www.engadget.com/2018/06/10/life-is-strange-awesome-adventures-captain-spirit/ |title='Life is Strange' returns with 'The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit' |last=Summers |first=Nick |website=[[Engadget]] |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |archivedate=10 June 2018 |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Polygon">{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2018/6/10/17446838/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-microsoft-e3-2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180610211015/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2018/6/10/17446838/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-microsoft-e3-2018 |title=The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit is a ‘100 percent free’ game in the Life is Strange universe |last=Kuchera |first=Ben |website=[[Polygon (magazine)|Polygon]] |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |archivedate=10 June 2018 |deadurl=no}}</ref> ''[[Life Is Strange 2]]'' was released on 27 September 2018,<ref name="Phillips-Jun2018">{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-06-22-life-is-strange-2s-first-episode-has-a-release-date|title=Life is Strange 2's first episode has a release date|first=Tom|last=Phillips|date=22 June 2018|website=[[Eurogamer]]}}</ref> featuring a new location and cast of characters.<ref name="n3w">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/24/8838761/life-is-strange-season-2-new-cast |title=Life is Strange's second season would star a new cast (if it happened) |first=Megan |last=Farokhmanesh |date=24 June 2015 |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201154029/http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/24/8838761/life-is-strange-season-2-new-cast |archivedate=1 December 2016}}</ref> A four-issue comic book series of the same name, set after the "Sacrifice Arcadia Bay" ending of the game, was released by [[Titan Comics]] in November 2018.<ref name="Knezevic-Mar2018">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/life-is-strange-comic-series-announced/1100-6457809/|title=Life Is Strange Comic Series Announced|first=Kevin|last=Knezevic|date=29 March 2018|website=[[GameSpot]]|archivedate=30 March 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180330030815/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/life-is-strange-comic-series-announced/1100-6457809/|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="Phillips-May2018">{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-05-03-life-is-strange-official-comic-continues-one-of-the-games-endings|title=Life is Strange official comic continues one of the game's endings|first=Tom|last=Phillips|date=3 May 2018|website=[[Eurogamer]]|archivedate=3 May 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503165127/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-05-03-life-is-strange-official-comic-continues-one-of-the-games-endings|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="Nieves-Jul2018">{{cite web|url=http://www.comicsbeat.com/sdcc18-titan-finally-gives-more-life-is-strange-details/|title=SDCC’18: Titan Finally Announces LIFE IS STRANGE Creative Team Details|first=Davey|last=Nieves|date=21 July 2018|website=[[Comics Beat]]|archivedate=21 July 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721181157/http://www.comicsbeat.com/sdcc18-titan-finally-gives-more-life-is-strange-details/|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was written by [[Emma Vieceli]], with interior and cover art by Claudia Leonardi and colors by Andrea Izzo.<ref name="Nieves-Jul2018" /> Square Enix also partnered with Titan Comics to produce ''Life Is Strange: Welcome to Blackwell Academy'', a book about Blackwell Academy written by [[Matt Forbeck]].<ref name="Riaz-Sep2018">{{cite web|url=https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2018/09/03/return-to-arcadia-bay-in-upcoming-life-is-strange-welcome-to-blackwell-academy/311036/|title=Return to Arcadia Bay in Upcoming Life Is Strange: Welcome to Blackwell Academy|first=Adnan|last=Riaz|date=3 September 2018|website=[[Hardcore Gamer]]|archivedate=4 September 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180904110407/https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2018/09/03/return-to-arcadia-bay-in-upcoming-life-is-strange-welcome-to-blackwell-academy/311036/|deadurl=no|df=dmy-all|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref>

