{{nihongo|'''Yamaguchi Prefectural Museum of Art'''|山口県立美術館|Yamaguchi Kenritsu Bijutsukan}}, in [[Yamaguchi, Yamaguchi|Yamaguchi City]] is the main art gallery of [[Yamaguchi Prefecture]], Japan.

Opened in 1979, the gallery has a permanent collection, part of which is exhibited at any one time, and also hosts special exhibitions.

The gallery's photographic collection includes an extensive collection of the works of [[Katsuji Fukuda]]. Its major photographic exhibitions have included three that showed work after the war: in 1989, an exhibition of eleven photographers of 1965&ndash;75; in 1990, of twelve photographers of 1945&ndash;55; and in 1991, of eleven photographers of 1955&ndash;65. The permanent photographic collection includes works by [[Hisae Imai]], [[Takeji Iwamiya]], [[Yutaka Takanashi]], and [[Toyoko Tokiwa]].

The museum is at Kameyama-chō <!-- Or is it Kameyama-machi? --> 3&ndash;1, Yamaguchi-shi.

